cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "DED Mémoriel Filter: Selective Inference Without Fine-Tuning"
authors:
  - family-names: Renno
    given-names: François
    affiliation: "Synoptisme Research Initiative"
    country: TH
repository-code: "https://github.com/HarmoIA/DED-memoriel"
url: "https://github.com/HarmoIA/DED-memoriel"
license: MIT
version: "1.0.0-simulation"
date-released: "2026-06-06"
keywords:
  - hallucination
  - selective inference
  - entropy
  - LLM
  - abstention
  - uncertainty routing
  - no fine-tuning
  - simulation
abstract: >
  DED Mémoriel Filter is a lightweight inference wrapper that transforms
  entropy signals from LLM logits into structured selective-inference
  and abstention decisions. The method is designed to operate without
  fine-tuning, external retrieval, or model-weight modification.
notes: >
  Preliminary results are based on calibrated simulated distributions
  using TruthfulQA N=817 assumptions. These results do not yet constitute
  experimental validation on real logits. Real-logit validation on
  Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3 is planned.
